.api
  h3 C Addons
  :markdown
    - Node.js reference http://nodejs.org/api/addons.html

    Not applicable. Extensions to Nodyn can be written in Java, Javascript, JRuby,
    Python or any other language supported by vert.x.

.api
  h3 Child Processes
  :markdown
    - Node.js reference http://nodejs.org/api/child_process.html

    Deferred. Since Nodyn runs on the JVM, any implementation we provide will not
    be actually spawning new process. It will instead probably use the Vert.x
    platform APIs to simulate `fork()` and `spawn()`.

.api
  h3 Cluster
  :markdown
    - Node.js reference http://nodejs.org/api/cluster.html

    Node.js clustering is not networked clustering, but rather running multiple
    instances of a Node.js app on a single machine in order to take advantage
    of the processor cores available on that machine. This API will likely be
    implemented with the Vert.x platform API, similar to Child Processes.

    Networked clustering, which Node.js does not provide an API for, is handled
    in Nodyn through vert.x builtin clustering, which itself uses
    [hazelcast](http://www.hazelcast.com/) for the implementation. Vert.x
    does not yet expose clustering data or an API.

